channel.title: My Build
channel.description:
I'm working on a new build which i am quite happy about. The only think killing me right now is the prices. I have considered waiting for USB3, at which time a lot of these components would go down in price. However, I have a feeling by the I wouldn't want this anymore as new chipsets and hardware would be on the way.
I'm looking to cut off about $200 or atleast close to that. Please note that although I give you the newegg link for each component, I am not buying off newegg and therefore working off of the actual prices not their deals.
Components:
Video Card: 200$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16814130370
Processor: 290$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16819115202
Memory: 77$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16820104005
Hard Drive: 70$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16822136320
Power Supply: 160$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16817189016
Mother Board: 290$ http://www.newegg.com/Product/Product.aspx?Item=N82E16813131365
Total USD: $1087.00 Total CAD: $1261.00
All prices rounded up!
Cheers!
